August 21, 1997
For questions or problems contact Kim Wilkins in the Washington office.
kwilkins@gensym.com 703-266-0203.
One can select a cooler and clone it to create a new cooler. Select cooling to turn it on; select off to turn it off.

Each communication link adds 200 degrees of heat. The satellite has 100 degrees of heat initally. Each cooler decreases the heat by 200 degrees. The satellite cannot exceed 600 degrees without internal damage.

g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.LABEL: OFF
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.CONDITION: the status of the item is on
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.ACTION: conclude that the status of the item is off

g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.LABEL: COOLING
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.CONDITION: the status of the item is off
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.ACTION: conclude that the status of the item is on

g2:c.RULE.g2:a.TEXT: if the temperature of s701 > max-temperature and the status of cooler-2 is off then conclude that the status of cooler-2 is on and start message("Temperature of satellite has exceeded maximum and cooler-2 has been activated")
for any cooler c whenever the status s of c receives a value then change the signal icon-color of c to (if s is on then the symbol green else if s is off then the symbol yellow else the symbol red)

g2:c.PROCEDURE.g2:a.TEXT: calculate-heat () begin conclude that the temperature of s701 = 100; invoke calculate-heat rules end

g2:c.RULE.g2:a.TEXT: for any cooler c if the status of c is on then conclude that the temperature of s701 = the temperature of s701 - 200
for any city b connected to big-switch unconditionally conclude that the temperature of s701 = the temperature of s701 + 200

g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.LABEL: Simulate COOLER-1 Failure
g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.ACTION: conclude that the status of cooler-1 is broken

g2:c.PROCEDURE.g2:a.TEXT: message(m:text) begin change the text of system-messages to m; wait for 5 seconds; change the text of system-messages to "No Messages" end

g2:c.FREE-TEXT.g2:a.TEXT:
In End-user mode, one can select a site and it will clone it. One can also clone a satellite and connect it to some sites. The satellites can be refueled and moved by selecting them.
To do the flare demo: (1) cooler 1 is on, cooler 2 is off; (2) 3 communication links; (3) select flare
Cooler 1 will disabled when the solar flare hits, a temperature spike will occur above 600 degrees, and the backup cooler, Cooler 2, will be turned on, restoring the temperature to below the threshold.

g2:c.RULE.g2:a.TEXT: initially show the subworkspace of world

g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.LABEL: REFUEL
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.ACTION: conclude that the fuel of the item = 800

g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.LABEL: STOP
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.CONDITION: (the move of the item is left or the move of the item is right) and the fuel of the item > 0
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.ACTION: conclude that the move of the item is stop

g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.LABEL: RIGHT
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.CONDITION: (the move of the item is left or the move of the item is stop) and the fuel of the item > 0
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.ACTION: conclude that the move of the item is right

g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.LABEL: LEFT
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.CONDITION: (the move of the item is right or the move of the item is stop) and the fuel of the item > 0
g2:c.USER-MENU-CHOICE.g2:a.ACTION: conclude that the move of the item is left

g2:c.RULE.g2:a.TEXT: for any solar-flare s if the distance between s and s701 < 100 then conclude that the status of cooler-1 is broken and conclude that the move of s701 is stop and delete s
for any building b connected to any satellite unconditionally change the beacon icon-color of b to (if the beacon icon-color of b is red then the symbol yellow else the symbol red)
for any solar-flare s unconditionally move s by (10,0)
whenever the fuel of s701 receives a value and when the fuel of s701 <= 0 then change the signal icon-color of fuel-tank-1 to red
if the fuel of s701 < 300 and the fuel of s701 > 0 then change the signal icon-color of fuel-tank-1 to orange
for any satellite s if the move of s is left and the fuel of s > 0 then move s by (-10,0) and conclude that the fuel of s = the fuel of s - 10
for any satellite s if the move of s is right and the fuel of s > 0 then move s by (10,0) and conclude that the fuel of s = the fuel of s - 10

g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.LABEL: Refuel
g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.ACTION: conclude that the fuel of s701 = 800 and change the signal icon-color of fuel-tank-1 to green

g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.LABEL: Move Satellite Right
g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.ACTION: conclude that the move of s701 is right

g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.LABEL: Stop Satellite Movement
g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.ACTION: conclude that the move of s701 is stop

g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.LABEL: Move Satellite Left
g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.ACTION: conclude that the move of s701 is left

g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.LABEL: Flare
g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.ACTION: in order create a solar-flare s and transfer s to the subworkspace of world and move s to (the item-x-position of s701 - 300, the item-y-position of s701)

g2:c.FREE-TEXT.g2:a.TEXT:
The red crosses are cities. The blue boxes are networks.
By moving the blue boxes around and selecting MAKE CONNECTIONS one can reconfigure the connections.
If the distance between a blue box and a red cross is more than 100 pixels than no connection will be made.

g2:c.PROCEDURE.g2:a.TEXT: delete-connections() c: class city; s: class switch-connection ; begin for c = each city upon the subworkspace of communication-subsystem do for s = each switch-connection connected to c do delete s removing connection stubs end end end

g2:c.RULE.g2:a.TEXT: for any connection c connected to big-switch unconditionally change the inner stripe-color of c to (if the inner stripe-color of c is yellow then the symbol blue else the symbol yellow)

g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.LABEL: Make Connections
g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.ACTION: in order start delete-connections () and start nearest-flag () and start make-connection (abc, 60, 40) and start make-connection (cbs, 100, 40) and start make-connection (nbc, 140, 40)

g2:c.RULE.g2:a.TEXT: for any city c upon the subworkspace of communication-subsystem for any switch connected to c unconditionally start charging(c)
